    • Constructor Detail

      • FrameMap

        public FrameMap()
        Constructs the FrameMap. Initializes its internal map with an empty concurrent map with weak keys. Weak keys mean that keys will be compared by ==, not by equals().

    • Method Detail

      • put

        public void put(Object pageObject,
                FramePath framePath)
        Puts another entry in the frame dictionary.
        Parameters:
        pageObject - PageObject that has an associated frame.
        framePath - Frame path associated with the PageObject.

      • get

        public FramePath get(Object pageObject)
        Parameters:
        pageObject - PageObjects for which to search for associated FramePath.
        Returns:
        Frame info associated with the PageObject fetched from the frame dictionary. If the entry is currently missing from the dictionary, get returns the default FramePath.
